This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on image restoration using generative adversarial networks. The use of Resnet architecture also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of conditional GANs, which may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of adversarial training may also suggest the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of datasets such as MNIST, CIFAR10/100, and CELEBA may suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
